    <td class="roweven" valign="top" width="2000">I have finally added MRU soring support with the popular demand :) <br><br>- Now you can specify the sorting method to be by MRU files. To make mru the default order, place this line in your vimrc: <br><br>let g:selBufDefaultSortOrder = &quot;mru&quot; <br><br>You can also use SBBufToHead and SBBufToTail commands with a buffer number argument to move the specified buffer to the starting and ending of the MRU list. <br><br>- If you make any changes to the configuration, you can use the new command SBInitialize to reconfigure the internal data of selectbuf.vim. <br><br>- Fixed some misc. bugs. <br>- FIxed the broken save/restore window settings (after converting to 6.0). Now even the vertically split windows are restored correctly. <br><br>Note that you need the new improved script genutils.vim instead of the older bufNwinUtils.vim. Download it from <br><br><a target="_blank" href="http://vim.sourceforge.net/scripts/script.php?script_id=197">http://vim.sourceforge.net/scripts/script.php?script_id=197</A> <br><br>Also you need the new improved multvals.vim instead of the older lightWeightArray.vim. Download it from:<br><br><a target="_blank" href="http://vim.sourceforge.net/scripts/script.php?script_id=171">http://vim.sourceforge.net/scripts/script.php?script_id=171</A></td>
